<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Eriogonum</i> <i>fasciculatum</i> and <i>Salvia</i> <i>apiana</i> are co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Adenostoma</i> <i>fasciculatum</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>greggii</i>, <i>Ceanothus</i> <i>leucodermis</i>, <i>Gutierrezia</i> <i>sarothrae</i>, <i>Hesperoyucca</i> <i>whipplei</i>, <i>Heteromeles</i> <i>arbutifolia</i>, <i>Keckiella</i> <i>antirrhinoides</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>scoparius</i>, <i>Malosma</i> <i>laurina</i> and <i>Quercus</i> <i>berberidifolia</i>. Emergent trees may be present at low cover, including <i>Quercus</i> <i>agrifolia</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 2.5 m; canopy intermittent. Herbaceous layer variable, may be grassy. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Eriogonum fasciculatum</i> and <i>Salvia apiana</i> are both 30-60% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Gordon and White 1994).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Bouldery south-facing slopes. Soils are usually sandy loams.  </div>
</div>

        
